<paragraph base="F45930237" id="IFRS16_B34"><paranum>B34</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IFRS 16"/><data name="paranum" value="B34"/></prolog><body><p id="IFRS16_P0515">In determining the <xref base="F45929725" href="IFRS16_APPA.dita#IFRS16_APPA/IFRS16_P0376">lease term<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0218"/></ph></xref> and assessing the length of the non-cancellable period of a <xref base="F45929685" href="IFRS16_APPA.dita#IFRS16_APPA/IFRS16_P0363">lease<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0214"/></ph></xref>, an entity shall apply the definition of a <xref base="F45929889" href="IFRS16_APPA.dita#IFRS16_APPA/IFRS16_P0398">contract<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0049"/></ph></xref> and determine the period for which the contract is enforceable. A lease is no longer enforceable when the <xref base="F45929736" href="IFRS16_APPA.dita#IFRS16_APPA/IFRS16_P0380">lessee<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0220"/></ph></xref> and the <xref base="F45929747" href="IFRS16_APPA.dita#IFRS16_APPA/IFRS16_P0382">lessor<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0222"/></ph></xref> each has the right to terminate the lease without permission from the other party with no more than an insignificant penalty.</p></body></paragraph>